# E-State — Testing Rules

Extends [.cursor/rules/common-testing.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/common-testing.mdc) and [.cursor/skills/tdd-workflow/SKILL.md](mdc:.cursor/skills/tdd-workflow/SKILL.md). 80 %+ coverage required.

## Required test tiers

1. **Unit** — normalizers in `ingest/`, pure functions in `matcher/detectors/`, React components in isolation.
2. **Contract** — one `tests/api/test_<router>.py` per FastAPI router, exercising the DTOs declared in [docs/api-contract.md](mdc:docs/api-contract.md).
3. **E2E** — Playwright covering one happy path per role from [docs/user-flows.md](mdc:docs/user-flows.md):
   - `e2e/back-office/upload-and-resolve.spec.ts`
   - `e2e/inspector/visit-flow.spec.ts`
   - `e2e/citizen/lookup.spec.ts`

## Matcher-specific (extends `e-state-data-matcher`)

- Every detector has a dedicated test file `tests/matcher/test_<detector>.py` with the three scenarios (`fires_on_positive_sample`, `ignores_negative_sample`, `is_idempotent`).
- Fixtures live under `services/api/tests/fixtures/` and must stay ≤ 30 rows each.
- `tests/test_pipeline_real_data.py` runs against the full real dataset and asserts the baselines in `tests/baselines.json`.
- When dataset baselines drift intentionally, update `baselines.json` and [docs/sample-findings.md](mdc:docs/sample-findings.md) together.

## PII tests (extends `e-state-pii`)

Required checks in `tests/security/test_pii.py`:

- No endpoint accepts `tax_id` via query string (asserted by crawling the OpenAPI doc).
- `mask_tax_id("2247237363") == "***7363"`.
- Logs produced during a citizen lookup contain no unmasked tax IDs (caplog assertion).

## Web tests

- Unit: Vitest + React Testing Library. Snapshot tests are discouraged; prefer role-based queries.
- E2E: Playwright with Page Object Model under `apps/web/tests/pages/`.
- Accessibility: `@axe-core/playwright` runs on every E2E path; zero serious violations allowed.

## Determinism

- Tests must not rely on wall-clock time; inject a `Clock` port.
- Random seeds are fixed where randomness applies (none in the matcher; only in generated fixture factories).

## CI guardrails

- `pytest --cov --cov-fail-under=80`.
- `npm test -- --coverage` (Vitest) with line coverage ≥ 80 % once a `test` script exists in `apps/web/package.json`; until then `npm run build` must pass on CI.
- E2E runs on every PR against an ephemeral environment that seeds the demo dataset automatically (see `docs/setup.md`).
